<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>In ZF 1.9 RC there is an attempt to fix the PHP 5.3.0 bug involving MYSQL_ATTR_INIT_COMMAND not being defined.
The fix replaces the constant with the value 1002.
As commented in the PHP bug reports, this fix does not work on a Windows x64/MySQL 5.1.36/PHP 5.3.0 0 just an example.
There is no longer a parse error but the effect does not occur.</p>

<p>The fix should attempt to run a SET NAMES command when first connecting to the database.
This or wait for the PHP fix :)</p>

<p>Thanks!</p>

